<statement>
<p>Suppose enrollment in a class was 76 in the fall and 77 in the following spring.</p>
<p>It was a <fillin characters="20" /> percent </p>
<p><ol style="list-style-type:upper-alpha"><li>decrease</li> 
<li>increase</li> 
</ol></p>



</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>1</li><li>B: increase</li></ul></p><p>Because 77 is bigger than 76 it is a percent increase.</p>
<p>The percent increase is <m>\displaystyle{100}{\left(\frac{{{77}-{76}}}{{76}}\right)}={100}\cdot\frac{{1}}{{76}}\approx{1}\%</m>.</p>
</solution>
</myopenmath>

